# Livewire 4 Best Practices

## Component Organization
- Store all Livewire SFC in `resources/views/components/frontend/`
- Use kebab-case for component names in Blade: `@livewire('frontend.album-card')`
- Use PascalCase for component classes internally

## Property Management
- Use public properties for reactive data
- Use `#[Computed]` for expensive operations that don't change often
- Avoid storing Eloquent models directly; use IDs instead

## Event Communication
- Use `$this->dispatch()` for upward communication
- Use `#[On]` attribute for listening to events
- Prefix custom events with domain: `album-created`, `filter-changed`

## Performance Optimization
- Use `wire:key` in loops with unique identifiers
- Use `wire:model.live` for real-time updates only when needed
- Use `data-loading` attributes for loading states

## Testing Requirements
- Write tests for all public methods
- Test event dispatching and handling
- Test computed properties with different states

## Example Validation Rule
```blade
<?php
new class extends Component {
    public $album = [
        'title' => '',
        'description' => '',
    ];

    public function save()
    {
        $this->validate([
            'album.title' => 'required|string|max:255',
            'album.description' => 'nullable|string|max:1000',
        ]);

        // save logic
    }
};
?>
```
